1
00:00:05,171 --> 00:00:10,552
<i>This is the fifth case this year</i>
<i>of a girl being found strangled to death.</i>

2
00:00:11,052 --> 00:00:12,762
<i>According to investigators,</i>

3
00:00:12,846 --> 00:00:15,932
<i>they view these repeated cases as linked</i>

4
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:17,934
<i>and are investigating accordingly.</i>

5
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:23,648
What? You're going to be a dad?

6
00:00:23,732 --> 00:00:24,733
Yes.

7
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:25,984
Congratulations!

8
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:27,068
Congratulations!

9
00:00:27,152 --> 00:00:27,986
Thank you.

10
00:00:28,069 --> 00:00:30,613
I had no idea.
You should have told us!

11
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:31,531
Sorry.

12
00:00:31,614 --> 00:00:34,159
Dr. Takamori,
I bet you'll be a great father.

13
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:35,910
I wonder.

14
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:37,037
We have to celebrate.

15
00:00:37,120 --> 00:00:38,371
No, you don't have to.

16
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:40,206
A pre-celebration drink.
A big one!

17
00:00:40,290 --> 00:00:42,709
- You just want to drink.
- No, I don't!

18
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:44,586
Dr. Masumi is on vacation, right?

19
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:45,712
Now is our chance.

20
00:00:47,088 --> 00:00:48,965
Hello, this is Medical Examiner Japan.

21
00:00:49,048 --> 00:00:51,718
How does the mindset
of becoming a father feel?

22
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:53,052
I'm not sure.

23
00:00:53,136 --> 00:00:54,471
It hasn't really sunk in yet.

24
00:00:54,554 --> 00:00:55,889
When is the due date?

25
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:57,515
For now, it's next weekend.

26
00:00:57,599 --> 00:00:58,558
Really?

27
00:00:58,641 --> 00:01:00,143
Hey, excuse me.

28
00:01:00,226 --> 00:01:02,771
We got a request
for an examination of a living person.

29
00:01:03,772 --> 00:01:07,650
A child suspected of being abused
was in an accident.

30
00:01:10,612 --> 00:01:12,739
<i>Clinical forensic medicine, right?</i>

31
00:01:12,822 --> 00:01:14,032
Yes.

32
00:01:14,115 --> 00:01:16,201
It's rare, isn't it?

33
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:19,287
Until now, we've only done
examinations on bodies.

34
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:21,247
With domestic violence, abuse,

35
00:01:21,331 --> 00:01:24,918
or other special cases, we sometimes
get asked to do an examination.

36
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:26,628
What should we do?

37
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:27,796
<i>Unfortunately,</i>

38
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,714
I can't come back yet.

39
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:33,510
Could you all handle it by yourself?

40
00:01:33,593 --> 00:01:36,596
What? Without you?

41
00:01:37,096 --> 00:01:40,517
Clinical forensic medicine
is Dr. Takamori's specialty.

42
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,435
<i>I'll let him handle it.</i>

43
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:48,066
I understand.

44
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:50,568
All right, then. Thank you.

45
00:01:53,988 --> 00:01:55,156
That's unusual.

46
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:57,158
Dr. Masumi never dumps a job
on someone else.

47
00:01:57,242 --> 00:01:58,701
<i>That's true.</i>

48
00:01:59,285 --> 00:02:00,829
<i>I wonder where he's going.</i>

49
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:07,794
Sorry we're late.

50
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:10,171
Huh? That doctor isn't here today?

51
00:02:10,255 --> 00:02:12,590
He couldn't quite make it today.

52
00:02:12,674 --> 00:02:14,259
Well, that helps.

53
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:20,431
Explain it to them.

54
00:02:20,515 --> 00:02:21,349
Yes, ma'am.

55
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:24,144
The victim is ten-year-old Kanata Togawa.

56
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:28,481
A neighbor found him collapsed here,
and he was rushed to the hospital.

57
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:32,193
He still hasn't regained consciousness
and is receiving treatment.

58
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:35,572
We don't know yet
if it was an accident or a crime.

59
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:42,328
What kind of findings suggest abuse?

60
00:02:42,412 --> 00:02:45,623
Bruises all over his body.
On his back, his arms, everywhere.

61
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:48,459
But there were no reports
to the child consultation center.

62
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:51,462
Also, I don't think it's relevant,

63
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:53,339
but just to let you know…

64
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:54,257
You're okay.

65
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:55,258
The monster…

66
00:02:56,217 --> 00:02:58,177
The monster is coming.

67
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:01,806
The black monster…

68
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:04,642
He said that and then lost consciousness.

69
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:05,727
Monster?

70
00:03:06,978 --> 00:03:08,396
We found a knife!

71
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:17,363
Maybe he was attacked with this
by the person who was abusing him,

72
00:03:17,447 --> 00:03:18,740
and then fell from here?

73
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:21,326
First, we need to find out
if there really was abuse.

74
00:03:21,409 --> 00:03:22,243
Yes, ma'am.

75
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,371
Just imagining it

76
00:03:26,331 --> 00:03:27,582
is painful.

77
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:40,803
Come in.

78
00:03:41,721 --> 00:03:42,931
Excuse me.

79
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:44,641
I'm Kiryu from MEJ.

80
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:45,892
I'm Takamori.

81
00:03:45,975 --> 00:03:50,313
We received a request for an examination
because there's a suspicion of abuse.

82
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:53,733
He hit his head quite hard,
so please be careful.

83
00:03:53,816 --> 00:03:54,817
Yes, sir.

84
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:01,032
Kanata…

85
00:04:02,992 --> 00:04:04,118
I'm sorry.

86
00:04:06,371 --> 00:04:07,372
Please.

87
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:08,289
Okay.

88
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:39,195
Are you all right?

89
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:42,156
It's nothing.

90
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:52,375
Are you Kanata's mother?

91
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:03,303
I was at my part-time job
when I got the call.

92
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:05,555
You must have been shocked.

93
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:07,098
Yes.

94
00:05:08,641 --> 00:05:11,686
I'm sorry, but it seems
there are marks on Kanata's body

95
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:16,024
that were unrelated to the accident.

96
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:18,359
Do you have any idea what they might be?

97
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:22,864
Ms. Togawa?

98
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:25,241
I don't know.

99
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:26,576
I'm sorry.

100
00:05:27,243 --> 00:05:29,579
Was Kanata at home alone today?

101
00:05:30,163 --> 00:05:31,664
I think so.

102
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,583
Sorry for asking,

103
00:05:33,666 --> 00:05:36,627
but you were divorced
five years ago, right?

104
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:39,922
Are you living alone with Kanata now?

105
00:05:41,090 --> 00:05:42,467
For the most part, yes.

106
00:05:42,550 --> 00:05:43,426
For the most part?

107
00:05:44,093 --> 00:05:47,764
The person I'm dating
also comes over sometimes.

108
00:05:50,516 --> 00:05:52,769
Where is that person now?

109
00:05:53,352 --> 00:05:55,396
I can't get in touch with him right now.

110
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,523
I think he'll be back soon, though.

111
00:05:58,107 --> 00:06:00,693
Could you tell me more about him?

112
00:06:02,737 --> 00:06:03,821
Yes.

113
00:06:04,655 --> 00:06:08,034
Kanata fell down the stairs
for some reason.

114
00:06:08,117 --> 00:06:10,870
He hit his head
on the landing midway down the stairs,

115
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:14,165
resulting in a cerebral contusion
and an acute subdural hematoma.

116
00:06:14,248 --> 00:06:15,500
There are also…

117
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:19,879
several other bruises
likely caused by hitting the stairs.

118
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:24,175
Those are the injuries from the fall.

119
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:27,553
So the rest are from abuse.

120
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:29,847
That's awful.

121
00:06:29,931 --> 00:06:31,974
Are these all abuse marks?

122
00:06:33,184 --> 00:06:34,602
I think so.

123
00:06:34,685 --> 00:06:36,646
The bruise marks can be covered up

124
00:06:36,729 --> 00:06:39,398
and are a characteristic of child abuse.

125
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:42,777
There are many scar patches
and keloids on his back, too.

126
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,113
Those are old wounds.

127
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:48,533
These wounds on his arm
look fairly new, though.

128
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:52,495
Coexisting old and new wounds
is also a characteristic of abuse.

129
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:54,413
Doctor.

130
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:56,791
This might be irrelevant,

131
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:59,210
but when Kanata was being transported,

132
00:06:59,293 --> 00:07:01,337
<i>he said, "The black monster is coming."</i>

133
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:02,922
<i>He seemed afraid.</i>

134
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:05,007
The black monster?

135
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:09,595
Maybe the person who abused him
looked that terrifying to him.

136
00:07:10,513 --> 00:07:11,639
But isn't it strange?

137
00:07:11,722 --> 00:07:14,142
If he was beaten by someone
who was abusing him,

138
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:16,727
he would likely say
"I was beaten by the monster."

139
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:18,855
Instead he said, "The monster is coming."

140
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,731
- True.
- No.

141
00:07:20,815 --> 00:07:22,692
He hit his head and was confused.

142
00:07:22,775 --> 00:07:24,652
Well, sure, but…

143
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:25,611
Anyway,

144
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:28,948
let's first investigate
what Kanata's daily life was like.

145
00:07:29,907 --> 00:07:30,867
- Okay.
- Okay.

146
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:47,550
Come in.

147
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,346
Excuse me.

148
00:07:59,687 --> 00:08:01,063
Long time no see.

149
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:02,815
Professor Kujo.

150
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:08,112
Has it been 15 years already?

151
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:11,991
A lot of time has passed, hasn't it?

152
00:08:13,784 --> 00:08:15,077
I heard…

153
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:17,163
I heard you're now working

154
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:20,917
at a death investigation facility
established by the Ministry.

155
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:21,876
Yes.

156
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:26,297
Professor, how is your health?

157
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:31,385
The cancer has spread all over.

158
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:33,930
They say I have three months left.

159
00:08:37,308 --> 00:08:39,477
I've lived long enough.

160
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:41,854
I'll let myself…

161
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:46,108
relax here for a little while longer.

162
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:51,447
You mean Ms. Togawa from 401, right?

163
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:53,616
I've heard screaming and things before.

164
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:55,201
What kind of screaming?

165
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:58,162
In the middle of the night,
suddenly, like "wahh!"

166
00:08:58,663 --> 00:09:01,249
I couldn't tell
what they were saying, though.

167
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:03,459
It didn't use to be like that, though.

168
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:06,712
The mom started dating
a scary-looking guy.

169
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:07,964
That's when it started.

170
00:09:08,506 --> 00:09:12,051
I saw Kanata
crying a lot in the park once.

171
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:14,470
How did Kanata look to you?

172
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:15,555
He was terrified.

173
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:17,890
He was screaming.

174
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:19,767
I felt so bad for him.

175
00:09:22,562 --> 00:09:24,272
I heard from the detective.

176
00:09:24,772 --> 00:09:25,982
I was shocked.

177
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:28,859
To think that Kanata
would have an accident like that.

178
00:09:31,153 --> 00:09:34,365
Mr. Kamijo, since the divorce,
have you seen Kanata?

179
00:09:35,324 --> 00:09:37,743
I haven't seen him for years.

180
00:09:39,328 --> 00:09:40,746
We divorced

181
00:09:41,747 --> 00:09:44,250
because of my affair.

182
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,085
I didn't feel like I could face him.

183
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:48,129
Sir…

184
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:52,091
There's also a suspicion
that Kanata was being abused.

185
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:53,968
Do you know anything about that?

186
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:56,846
I've heard rumors.

187
00:09:57,638 --> 00:09:58,639
I was worried.

188
00:09:59,223 --> 00:10:00,099
Rumors?

189
00:10:00,182 --> 00:10:03,060
Saya started dating a bad guy.

190
00:10:05,146 --> 00:10:07,064
If I had taken Kanata in,

191
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:08,774
this would never…

192
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:14,822
I should go see him.

193
00:10:15,948 --> 00:10:17,700
I could buy him some <i>kintsuba.</i>

194
00:10:19,994 --> 00:10:23,748
Even though he's a kid,
he loves Japanese sweets.

195
00:10:25,249 --> 00:10:27,209
I'm sure that would make him happy.

196
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:30,463
But maybe his tastes have changed by now.

197
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:33,591
I bet he has grown up.

198
00:10:36,677 --> 00:10:39,472
Ryoji Kida, 34 years old.
A construction worker.

199
00:10:39,555 --> 00:10:41,641
He's Saya Togawa's boyfriend.

200
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:44,644
We haven't been able
to contact Kida since the incident,

201
00:10:44,727 --> 00:10:47,772
and it seems he didn't show up
for work today either.

202
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:51,776
So the mother's boyfriend is the abuser.

203
00:10:51,859 --> 00:10:52,902
I think so.

204
00:10:53,653 --> 00:10:54,654
However…

205
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:56,113
What?

206
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:58,407
Regarding the knife that was found,

207
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:01,952
it seems only Kanata's fingerprints
were detected on it.

208
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:04,163
Kanata's? Not Kida's?

209
00:11:04,246 --> 00:11:05,122
Yes.

210
00:11:05,206 --> 00:11:06,582
And one more thing.

211
00:11:06,666 --> 00:11:07,500
What?

212
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:09,960
Well, it might not be relevant, actually.

213
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:11,253
Just say it.

214
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,171
Yes, ma'am.

215
00:11:13,506 --> 00:11:15,716
Well, about Kida…

216
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:19,637
It seems he was abused himself
in the past.

217
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:20,721
RYOJI KIDA

218
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:22,014
He was?

219
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:24,308
Ms. Kiryu said she heard it
from the police.

220
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:28,437
Apparently, he was quite severely abused
by his stepfather when he was a child.

221
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:31,899
Even though he was abused himself,
he abuses a child?

222
00:11:31,982 --> 00:11:34,318
Well, don't they say
people who were abused

223
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:37,988
tend to become abusers themselves
when they grow up?

224
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:40,991
Maybe because that's
the kind of parent they saw?

225
00:11:41,075 --> 00:11:43,536
A cycle of abuse, so to speak.

226
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:46,080
Taking the pain you suffered
out on a child…

227
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:47,998
Right…

228
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:08,060
I'm glad you took the time to come.

229
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:15,401
I was only able to get where I am
because of you, Professor.

230
00:12:17,319 --> 00:12:18,446
"Loved One."

231
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:24,368
How to face a body.

232
00:12:26,287 --> 00:12:27,538
To doubt common sense,

233
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:31,542
not to be bound by precedent,
and to have free thought.

234
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:38,632
I was captivated by this field of study
because of your words.

235
00:12:39,925 --> 00:12:41,886
You remember them well.

236
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:43,512
But…

237
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:46,974
during that case,

238
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:50,102
you didn't do any of that, Professor.

239
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:04,575
The Shiramine serial femicide case.

240
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,038
You remember it, don't you?

241
00:13:11,415 --> 00:13:16,128
I intend to face that case once more.

242
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,298
Fifteen years ago…

243
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:20,925
SHIRAMINE SERIAL FEMICIDE CASE
RESEARCH DATA

244
00:13:21,008 --> 00:13:24,261
<i>…I ran away from that case.</i>

245
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:26,597
Even though I had doubts

246
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:28,933
about your autopsy results.

247
00:13:31,101 --> 00:13:32,603
At that time,

248
00:13:32,686 --> 00:13:36,774
I didn't have the power or the knowledge
to overturn it.

249
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:38,776
But now,

250
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:42,530
I might be able
to unravel the contradictions.

251
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,784
Please tell me, Professor.

252
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:51,664
What really happened
behind the scenes of that case?

253
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:04,843
Well, isn't this a rare visitor?

254
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,429
Kyoko.

255
00:14:08,305 --> 00:14:10,307
Don't push my father too hard.

256
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:17,189
I'm sorry for coming
at such a difficult time.

257
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:26,365
I'll come again.

258
00:14:27,449 --> 00:14:28,284
Okay.

259
00:14:44,049 --> 00:14:45,426
You're back.

260
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:49,179
How long will you be in Japan?

261
00:14:49,763 --> 00:14:51,348
For a while.

262
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:56,270
You haven't changed at all.

263
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:58,355
That's not true.

264
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:06,614
You've heard about my father, right?

265
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,325
He has little time left.

266
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:13,329
I want him

267
00:15:14,371 --> 00:15:17,207
to be able to forget everything
and pass away in peace.

268
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:24,089
The serial murders happening recently…

269
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:29,595
They're similar
to the Shiramine murder case.

270
00:15:29,678 --> 00:15:31,347
There might be a connection.

271
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:38,103
Even if there is a connection,

272
00:15:38,812 --> 00:15:40,898
it has nothing to do
with you or my father.

273
00:15:42,232 --> 00:15:43,609
Don't come back.

274
00:15:44,985 --> 00:15:46,445
You should forget it too.

275
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:09,134
<i>This is the fifth case this year</i>
<i>of a girl being found strangled to death.</i>

276
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:12,930
<i>They're similar</i>
<i>to the Shiramine murder case.</i>

277
00:16:13,013 --> 00:16:14,723
You should forget it too.

278
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,649
Kanata has apparently
been terrified at school

279
00:16:23,732 --> 00:16:26,151
for about a year,
saying he didn't want to go home.

280
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:30,781
That matches the time
Ms. Togawa started dating Kida.

281
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:32,741
It does.

282
00:16:33,534 --> 00:16:34,410
Detective Dojima.

283
00:16:34,493 --> 00:16:35,494
What?

284
00:16:35,577 --> 00:16:37,204
Kida has turned himself in.

285
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,710
Like I said,

286
00:16:42,793 --> 00:16:44,795
Kanata was being annoying.

287
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:47,214
He never listened to me,

288
00:16:47,297 --> 00:16:49,967
so sometimes I slapped him,
telling him to be quiet.

289
00:16:50,968 --> 00:16:52,553
It was the same that day.

290
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:55,055
He wouldn't stop crying,
and was bothering others.

291
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:56,890
<i>So,</i>

292
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:58,475
<i>I gave him a light push.</i>

293
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,149
I'm sorry for running away.

294
00:17:05,232 --> 00:17:06,692
But I just panicked.

295
00:17:06,775 --> 00:17:08,902
What about the knife we found
at the scene?

296
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:10,112
No idea.

297
00:17:11,321 --> 00:17:13,407
It's not related to the incident?

298
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:16,744
Calling it an incident or abuse…

299
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:19,455
All I did was discipline him a little.

300
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,665
Discipline, you say?

301
00:17:21,749 --> 00:17:22,791
That's right.

302
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:26,295
That was just a little discipline.

303
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:28,255
<i>This is just some discipline.</i>

304
00:17:28,338 --> 00:17:29,757
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

305
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:30,841
<i>Don't cry!</i>

306
00:17:30,924 --> 00:17:32,259
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

307
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:35,095
<i>I'm sorry!</i>

308
00:17:36,972 --> 00:17:38,098
Dr. Takamori?

309
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,977
Are you okay? Dr. Takamori?

310
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:44,438
Hey, are you okay?

311
00:17:44,521 --> 00:17:45,898
How is Kida?

312
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:48,484
He's in the holding cell now
and is being quiet.

313
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:50,778
He said he doesn't need
a lawyer or any visitors.

314
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:51,945
That's great, right?

315
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:53,405
The case was solved easily.

316
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:55,365
I don't think it's solved.

317
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:56,950
What?

318
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:08,629
Are you okay?

319
00:18:17,012 --> 00:18:18,555
I'm sorry.

320
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:19,848
No, not at all.

321
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:27,397
Go home for the day and get some rest.

322
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,484
We need you to get well soon.

323
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,569
Since you'll be a dad.

324
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:42,704
I don't have the confidence.

325
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:49,753
I was abused, too.

326
00:18:51,296 --> 00:18:52,506
A long time ago.

327
00:18:56,677 --> 00:18:58,428
By my stepfather.

328
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:04,226
When he got drunk, he would get violent.

329
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:09,356
I still have the scars.

330
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:12,734
They're on my back.

331
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:16,697
They're very similar to Kanata's scars.

332
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:22,995
I'm sorry for making you remember
something so unpleasant.

333
00:19:27,207 --> 00:19:28,709
I didn't remember it.

334
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:32,629
It's always in my head.

335
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,257
Kida…

336
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:41,180
was also abused by his parents.

337
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:46,143
And now,

338
00:19:46,768 --> 00:19:48,937
he's the one abusing a child.

339
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:54,818
I'm scared…

340
00:19:58,614 --> 00:20:00,032
that one day…

341
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:06,914
I might also end up raising
my hand against my own child.

342
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:09,458
No, you would never.

343
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:19,760
But maybe…

344
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:24,848
because you experienced that,

345
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,894
there is something you can do.

346
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:34,024
I think you're the one who understands

347
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:38,153
how much Kanata suffers

348
00:20:39,738 --> 00:20:41,907
better than anyone, Dr. Takamori.

349
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:01,635
I'm sorry…

350
00:21:04,054 --> 00:21:05,430
Kanata.

351
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:29,871
MY CHECKUP IS DONE
THEY SAID THE BABY IS VERY HEALTHY!

352
00:21:55,188 --> 00:21:56,606
<i>This is Masumi.</i>

353
00:21:57,816 --> 00:22:01,236
This is Takamori.
Sorry for calling while you're on leave.

354
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,530
<i>No, it's fine.</i>

355
00:22:04,239 --> 00:22:05,615
Did something happen?

356
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:14,458
I'm sorry for leaving
the investigation entirely to you.

357
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:17,544
I've heard about the situation
from Ms. Kiryu.

358
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:22,215
I don't know what to do.

359
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:27,304
The suspect turned himself in,

360
00:22:28,513 --> 00:22:30,807
but I feel like nothing
has been solved yet.

361
00:22:34,227 --> 00:22:37,773
I was wondering what you would do
in a situation like this.

362
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:41,735
<i>If it were me,</i>

363
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:44,821
<i>I would re-examine</i>
<i>the remaining contradictions.</i>

364
00:22:45,322 --> 00:22:46,948
Like, the wounds on the arm.

365
00:22:47,032 --> 00:22:51,036
<i>Those wounds were arranged in parallel</i>
<i>with a certain regularity.</i>

366
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:56,583
In cases of abuse, scars and bruises
would be scattered randomly,

367
00:22:56,666 --> 00:22:59,544
not perfectly parallel.

368
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:00,921
It doesn't add up.

369
00:23:03,965 --> 00:23:08,345
<i>But, please keep in mind,</i>
<i>this is just how I would do it.</i>

370
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:14,518
How one faces forensic medicine
is free and different for everyone.

371
00:23:15,727 --> 00:23:16,978
Dr. Takamori,

372
00:23:17,687 --> 00:23:20,690
how will you solve this mystery?

373
00:23:29,574 --> 00:23:32,035
Dr. Takamori is late, isn't he?

374
00:23:32,119 --> 00:23:33,829
There's no point in waiting.

375
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:35,664
Let's start with what we can do.

376
00:23:35,747 --> 00:23:37,833
Sorry, I'm late.

377
00:23:37,916 --> 00:23:39,417
Dr. Takamori.

378
00:23:39,501 --> 00:23:43,672
I've decided
to try and find the truth one more time.

379
00:23:45,715 --> 00:23:49,636
I've reclassified Kanata's scars
based on their characteristics.

380
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:52,889
Contusions on the head from the fall.

381
00:23:52,973 --> 00:23:55,809
Bruises and burn marks,
which suggest abuse.

382
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:58,478
And systematic wounds on the left arm.

383
00:23:58,562 --> 00:23:59,855
Looking at them like this,

384
00:23:59,938 --> 00:24:03,066
they each seem to be wounds
inflicted in different ways.

385
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:04,151
Right.

386
00:24:04,234 --> 00:24:05,527
That's easy to understand.

387
00:24:06,027 --> 00:24:09,197
So the arm wounds are the only ones
that are strange after all.

388
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:16,997
I want everyone to analyze
these arm wounds in detail.

389
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:17,914
Okay.

390
00:24:17,998 --> 00:24:18,832
Understood.

391
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:20,959
What about you?

392
00:24:21,835 --> 00:24:23,044
I…

393
00:24:28,341 --> 00:24:29,759
A long time ago,

394
00:24:30,594 --> 00:24:32,679
I was abused by my stepfather.

395
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:40,562
I looked back at my own experience.

396
00:24:41,897 --> 00:24:44,858
Abuse always happens inside the house.

397
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:47,611
I'm going to look for clues there.

398
00:24:51,531 --> 00:24:54,618
I'm sorry for having you come
all the way out here with us.

399
00:24:54,701 --> 00:24:57,370
It can't be helped,
since the police need to be present.

400
00:24:57,454 --> 00:24:58,788
It's a big help.

401
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:02,626
I want clues too.

402
00:25:09,424 --> 00:25:12,052
I'm sorry for taking up your time.

403
00:25:12,135 --> 00:25:16,264
Since it is such a serious case, we need
to investigate inside the home as well.

404
00:25:16,348 --> 00:25:20,060
I don't want to leave Kanata alone
for a long time…

405
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:22,270
We won't stay long.

406
00:25:28,360 --> 00:25:29,444
Is something wrong?

407
00:25:30,779 --> 00:25:32,113
It's not roughed up.

408
00:25:34,324 --> 00:25:35,158
What?

409
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:39,079
When there's abuse,

410
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:42,916
there are marks
on the walls and everywhere.

411
00:25:42,999 --> 00:25:46,503
From going on a rampage
and throwing things and stuff.

412
00:25:48,546 --> 00:25:49,839
That's how it was at my place.

413
00:25:54,511 --> 00:25:55,470
Here you go.

414
00:25:55,553 --> 00:25:57,138
Please, don't trouble yourself.

415
00:25:58,556 --> 00:25:59,849
Thank you very much.

416
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:01,351
Have some of this too.

417
00:26:02,769 --> 00:26:05,063
He likes them, so I bought some.

418
00:26:12,195 --> 00:26:13,738
Those are nice photos.

419
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:20,745
That was Kida's influence too.

420
00:26:21,579 --> 00:26:25,292
He does martial arts,
so he said he watches his calories

421
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:28,211
and chooses Japanese
sweets over Western ones,

422
00:26:28,878 --> 00:26:30,922
so Kanata started eating them to copy him.

423
00:26:31,589 --> 00:26:33,800
Forgive me for asking, Saya,

424
00:26:33,883 --> 00:26:38,221
but did you not notice that Kida
was committing abuse?

425
00:26:40,682 --> 00:26:41,850
Or perhaps,

426
00:26:42,517 --> 00:26:45,061
did you not think he was committing abuse?

427
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:48,857
I don't know.

428
00:26:50,775 --> 00:26:51,735
Well then,

429
00:26:51,818 --> 00:26:53,862
what about the "monster"?

430
00:26:54,904 --> 00:26:59,075
The "black monster" Kanata mentioned
when he was being transported.

431
00:26:59,659 --> 00:27:01,286
Do you have any ideas?

432
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:09,210
I only vaguely remember…

433
00:27:11,171 --> 00:27:13,798
I might have read him
a picture book about that.

434
00:27:14,382 --> 00:27:15,633
A picture book?

435
00:27:16,676 --> 00:27:17,969
THE BLACK MONSTER

436
00:27:18,053 --> 00:27:22,807
<i>The Black Monster,</i>
a picture book published in the '80s.

437
00:27:24,225 --> 00:27:25,560
One night,

438
00:27:25,643 --> 00:27:29,814
a black monster appears before a child
who does nothing but play pranks.

439
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:32,442
Eerie hands stretch out from the darkness

440
00:27:32,525 --> 00:27:34,736
and wrap around the child.

441
00:27:35,445 --> 00:27:37,989
He desperately resisted,
and drove it away.

442
00:27:38,073 --> 00:27:40,950
But after that,
every time he did something bad,

443
00:27:41,034 --> 00:27:44,037
the black hands
would wrap around the child again.

444
00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:46,498
In the end,

445
00:27:46,581 --> 00:27:49,918
the black hands wrapped around
the child's arms and wouldn't let go,

446
00:27:50,001 --> 00:27:53,505
and he finally ended up
becoming a black monster himself.

447
00:27:53,588 --> 00:27:54,881
The end.

448
00:27:55,382 --> 00:27:57,592
Why is it such a hopeless story?

449
00:27:58,968 --> 00:28:01,679
A lesson not to do bad things?

450
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:07,268
If the thing Kanata feared
was the monster from this picture book…

451
00:28:21,241 --> 00:28:22,325
Kanata?

452
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:24,953
Kanata!

453
00:28:27,664 --> 00:28:28,873
Kanata…

454
00:28:34,587 --> 00:28:35,797
Kanata,

455
00:28:36,631 --> 00:28:39,342
can you talk to us for just a little bit?

456
00:28:41,261 --> 00:28:42,137
Yes.

457
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,054
Thank you.

458
00:28:44,723 --> 00:28:47,851
Do you remember what happened
when you fell down the stairs?

459
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:57,068
I don't know.

460
00:28:57,861 --> 00:29:00,155
I don't really remember.

461
00:29:01,197 --> 00:29:02,323
I see.

462
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:07,620
It looks like you have quite
a few injuries besides your head.

463
00:29:09,372 --> 00:29:10,999
Where did you get hurt?

464
00:29:16,588 --> 00:29:20,425
Can I look at your wounds
for just a second?

465
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:22,343
Yes.

466
00:29:26,514 --> 00:29:27,432
Sorry.

467
00:29:34,689 --> 00:29:35,607
Kanata!

468
00:29:35,690 --> 00:29:37,859
I'm scared, I'm scared!

469
00:29:37,942 --> 00:29:39,402
The monster is coming!

470
00:29:39,486 --> 00:29:41,488
The black monster!

471
00:29:43,114 --> 00:29:44,199
Kanata!

472
00:29:47,076 --> 00:29:48,912
I'm sorry, that's enough for today.

473
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:51,164
Kanata.

474
00:29:51,247 --> 00:29:52,207
You'll be okay.

475
00:29:53,208 --> 00:29:55,084
Doctor, what's that?

476
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:57,587
This is Kanata's head MRI.

477
00:29:57,670 --> 00:30:00,548
- Something is bugging me.
- Bugging you?

478
00:30:01,549 --> 00:30:02,717
This.

479
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:04,636
What is it?

480
00:30:08,431 --> 00:30:12,268
<i>Those wounds were arranged in parallel</i>
<i>with a certain regularity.</i>

481
00:30:13,102 --> 00:30:14,312
<i>In the end,</i>

482
00:30:14,395 --> 00:30:17,148
<i>the black hands wrapped around</i>
<i>the child's arms and wouldn't let go,</i>

483
00:30:17,232 --> 00:30:19,776
<i>and he finally ended up</i>
<i>becoming a black monster himself.</i>

484
00:30:19,859 --> 00:30:21,319
<i>The black monster!</i>

485
00:30:23,738 --> 00:30:25,198
Dr. Takamori?

486
00:30:25,782 --> 00:30:26,825
Now…

487
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:29,536
the pieces might be coming together.

488
00:30:33,081 --> 00:30:35,458
What else do you want?
I already told you everything.

489
00:30:35,542 --> 00:30:36,835
No, you haven't.

490
00:30:36,918 --> 00:30:38,962
I need you to tell me the truth.

491
00:30:39,587 --> 00:30:40,505
What?

492
00:30:40,588 --> 00:30:45,426
You weren't the one abusing Kanata.

493
00:30:52,976 --> 00:30:55,103
How is Kanata doing?

494
00:30:56,396 --> 00:30:59,065
Are you not going to see him, Mr. Kamijo?

495
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:02,235
Well, even if I did…

496
00:31:03,152 --> 00:31:04,487
It was you, wasn't it?

497
00:31:05,530 --> 00:31:07,574
You were the one abusing Kanata.

498
00:31:09,617 --> 00:31:11,160
What kind of nonsense is that?

499
00:31:11,244 --> 00:31:13,580
Looking at Kanata's head MRI,

500
00:31:13,663 --> 00:31:16,749
there is slight atrophy
in the temporal and frontal lobes.

501
00:31:17,333 --> 00:31:18,209
Atrophy?

502
00:31:18,293 --> 00:31:22,380
This is a characteristic seen in children
who have been abused in the past.

503
00:31:22,463 --> 00:31:25,174
It is said that
the emotional scars received

504
00:31:25,258 --> 00:31:27,427
manifest in the brain.

505
00:31:29,178 --> 00:31:31,389
Kanata's scars are also unnatural.

506
00:31:31,472 --> 00:31:33,349
The wounds on his back and thighs

507
00:31:33,433 --> 00:31:36,227
<i>have a different color tone</i>
<i>compared to the others.</i>

508
00:31:36,311 --> 00:31:37,228
<i>Those wounds</i>

509
00:31:37,812 --> 00:31:41,649
might date back much further
than a year ago,

510
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:45,528
to before you even started dating Saya.

511
00:31:46,529 --> 00:31:47,822
In other words,

512
00:31:48,323 --> 00:31:50,909
he was being abused

513
00:31:51,618 --> 00:31:55,079
long before she met you.

514
00:31:55,163 --> 00:31:56,414
Mr. Kamijo,

515
00:31:57,332 --> 00:31:59,667
these are considered
wounds from past abuse

516
00:32:00,585 --> 00:32:02,837
that occurred when he was living with you.

517
00:32:04,297 --> 00:32:06,257
Stop joking around.

518
00:32:06,341 --> 00:32:07,300
Why would I--

519
00:32:07,383 --> 00:32:09,135
You said it the other day, didn't you?

520
00:32:09,218 --> 00:32:11,304
That Kanata likes <i>kintsuba.</i>

521
00:32:11,387 --> 00:32:12,805
Of course I know what my son--

522
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:17,268
Kanata only started liking <i>kintsuba</i>
after meeting Mr. Kida.

523
00:32:17,352 --> 00:32:19,395
That happened within the past year.

524
00:32:20,939 --> 00:32:24,233
You said you haven't seen him in years,
so how did you know?

525
00:32:26,152 --> 00:32:30,615
You've actually been seeing Kanata
over the past year, haven't you?

526
00:32:31,407 --> 00:32:32,659
<i>The question is,</i>

527
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:36,663
why are you protecting Kamijo,
when you have nothing to do with him?

528
00:32:39,123 --> 00:32:40,583
I don't know.

529
00:32:41,250 --> 00:32:42,877
I'm not protecting anybody.

530
00:32:42,961 --> 00:32:48,257
The important clue for us
was the parallel wounds

531
00:32:48,341 --> 00:32:50,718
<i>carved into Kanata's left arm.</i>

532
00:32:50,802 --> 00:32:52,845
Normally, if someone
continued to abuse a person,

533
00:32:52,929 --> 00:32:55,348
the wounds would be more random.

534
00:32:56,599 --> 00:32:57,934
But those wounds

535
00:32:58,434 --> 00:33:01,729
were placed systematically,
in the same spot

536
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:03,940
over and over again in the same way.

537
00:33:05,274 --> 00:33:07,986
They aren't scars
from abuse by another person.

538
00:33:09,404 --> 00:33:13,783
They're scars that Kanata
was inflicting on himself.

539
00:33:14,409 --> 00:33:16,577
<i>to stop the black monster from coming.</i>

540
00:33:16,661 --> 00:33:19,831
The black monster is coming… The monster…

541
00:33:22,041 --> 00:33:23,793
Three months ago,

542
00:33:23,876 --> 00:33:26,170
during a drinking session
with old friends,

543
00:33:26,254 --> 00:33:29,507
you apparently heard
that Saya had a new lover.

544
00:33:30,425 --> 00:33:33,761
You seemed to have become very jealous.

545
00:33:35,972 --> 00:33:37,807
- Coming!
<i>- So then…</i>

546
00:33:38,391 --> 00:33:40,309
<i>You went to Saya's home.</i>

547
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:44,272
Please leave.

548
00:33:44,355 --> 00:33:46,524
What's the big deal? I'm your ex-husband.

549
00:34:00,705 --> 00:34:02,206
Are you her new boyfriend?

550
00:34:03,249 --> 00:34:04,500
Please leave.

551
00:34:09,172 --> 00:34:10,757
You've grown, Kanata.

552
00:34:13,176 --> 00:34:14,093
Hey.

553
00:34:14,802 --> 00:34:17,638
Daddy's talking to you.
You should answer.

554
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:22,185
<i>Past memories of being beaten</i>
<i>flashed back to Kanata.</i>

555
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:27,857
<i>To resist the trauma,</i>
<i>so that the black monster wouldn't come,</i>

556
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,692
Kanata, it's okay.

557
00:34:29,776 --> 00:34:31,778
- The monster…
- Go away, now!

558
00:34:32,361 --> 00:34:34,030
I'm scared! Stop!

559
00:34:34,113 --> 00:34:35,198
Kanata!

560
00:34:35,281 --> 00:34:36,491
What is this?

561
00:34:36,574 --> 00:34:38,242
No, the monster!

562
00:34:38,326 --> 00:34:40,161
- Hey, Kanata!
- The monster…

563
00:34:42,747 --> 00:34:44,040
It's okay now.

564
00:34:44,123 --> 00:34:45,083
You're okay.

565
00:34:48,628 --> 00:34:49,504
All right!

566
00:34:50,254 --> 00:34:52,465
You're doing it. Go!

567
00:34:58,721 --> 00:35:00,348
I'm scared!

568
00:35:00,431 --> 00:35:02,183
- No!
- It's okay.

569
00:35:02,266 --> 00:35:04,352
- Should we do something?
- No! Stop!

570
00:35:04,435 --> 00:35:07,647
- You're okay!
<i>- Kanata's flashbacks kept coming back.</i>

571
00:35:08,648 --> 00:35:13,611
You wanted to help him somehow,
didn't you?

572
00:35:13,694 --> 00:35:15,154
If you're a man,

573
00:35:15,238 --> 00:35:18,324
you've got to become
strong enough to help your mom.

574
00:35:19,700 --> 00:35:21,202
- But…
- You can do it.

575
00:35:23,079 --> 00:35:24,247
Kanata,

576
00:35:25,206 --> 00:35:26,707
you're strong.

577
00:35:28,668 --> 00:35:31,504
I'm… strong?

578
00:35:31,587 --> 00:35:32,630
Yes.

579
00:35:37,677 --> 00:35:41,597
<i>Thanks to Mr. Kida,</i>
<i>Kanata gradually began to recover.</i>

580
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:44,642
But then the incident happened…

581
00:35:46,519 --> 00:35:49,272
because you came to Kanata's house again.

582
00:35:50,982 --> 00:35:52,066
Probably,

583
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:54,443
<i>what happened on that day was…</i>

584
00:35:55,194 --> 00:35:57,155
TOGAWA

585
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:02,827
What?

586
00:36:03,536 --> 00:36:04,954
Saya's not here?

587
00:36:05,037 --> 00:36:06,164
Where's Saya?

588
00:36:06,747 --> 00:36:07,748
Where did she go?

589
00:36:18,426 --> 00:36:19,635
I am…

590
00:36:21,429 --> 00:36:22,513
strong.

591
00:36:23,181 --> 00:36:24,265
<i>But…</i>

592
00:36:24,891 --> 00:36:26,267
<i>Kida's teachings…</i>

593
00:36:27,351 --> 00:36:29,020
<i>backfired.</i>

594
00:36:52,501 --> 00:36:54,086
Don't talk nonsense.

595
00:36:54,587 --> 00:36:55,838
It wasn't me.

596
00:36:56,672 --> 00:36:58,382
Saya's boyfriend has confessed.

597
00:36:59,467 --> 00:37:00,384
Yes.

598
00:37:03,512 --> 00:37:05,348
After being threatened by you.

599
00:37:08,726 --> 00:37:10,436
From my perspective,

600
00:37:10,519 --> 00:37:14,273
I just went to the house
and was almost stabbed to death.

601
00:37:15,066 --> 00:37:17,818
This is a clear case of attempted murder.

602
00:37:19,362 --> 00:37:20,988
You've got to be kidding me.

603
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:22,657
What about you abusing him?

604
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:25,326
You can't prove something
from that long ago.

605
00:37:26,869 --> 00:37:28,162
On the other hand,

606
00:37:28,871 --> 00:37:31,123
Kanata has strange delusions
and self-harms,

607
00:37:31,207 --> 00:37:33,626
and tries to stab people to death.

608
00:37:36,587 --> 00:37:38,047
He'll go to a detention center.

609
00:37:42,885 --> 00:37:45,012
Just say that you did it.

610
00:37:46,430 --> 00:37:48,099
If you want to save Kanata,

611
00:37:51,394 --> 00:37:52,728
you know what to do.

612
00:37:57,942 --> 00:37:59,068
Mr. Kida…

613
00:38:01,821 --> 00:38:02,989
You had no choice--

614
00:38:03,072 --> 00:38:04,115
I did it.

615
00:38:06,617 --> 00:38:08,035
That's enough, isn't it?

616
00:38:12,081 --> 00:38:13,374
Actually,

617
00:38:14,375 --> 00:38:15,960
before I came here…

618
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,964
Saya told me everything.

619
00:38:25,261 --> 00:38:27,430
I HAVE TO SAY I DID IT, FOR KANATA'S SAKE

620
00:38:27,513 --> 00:38:29,098
<i>After the incident,</i>

621
00:38:29,724 --> 00:38:32,977
<i>she was told</i>
<i>to match what you were going to say,</i>

622
00:38:33,561 --> 00:38:36,063
<i>and she has been hesitant about it</i>
<i>the entire time.</i>

623
00:38:37,148 --> 00:38:39,567
No matter what the police ask you,

624
00:38:40,276 --> 00:38:41,902
just say you don't know.

625
00:38:43,195 --> 00:38:44,697
What about Ryoji?

626
00:38:45,865 --> 00:38:47,199
Where is he?

627
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:49,535
He's okay.

628
00:38:50,786 --> 00:38:51,871
It'll be fine.

629
00:38:52,955 --> 00:38:54,040
<i>She wondered</i>

630
00:38:54,999 --> 00:38:57,168
<i>if this was really for the best.</i>

631
00:38:58,794 --> 00:39:00,671
There's no way this is a solution.

632
00:39:02,798 --> 00:39:05,760
After all, Kanata likes Ryoji, too.

633
00:39:11,474 --> 00:39:13,225
He really loves him.

634
00:39:16,896 --> 00:39:18,731
That's what Saya said.

635
00:39:24,820 --> 00:39:26,697
The one you were trying to protect

636
00:39:27,698 --> 00:39:29,450
and keep safe

637
00:39:31,202 --> 00:39:32,953
was Kanata, wasn't it?

638
00:39:48,844 --> 00:39:49,804
Yes?

639
00:39:51,722 --> 00:39:56,310
Do you understand how heartbreaking it is
to be beaten by your own parent?

640
00:39:58,604 --> 00:40:01,690
Scars from being beaten by
someone you want to be loved by most

641
00:40:03,359 --> 00:40:05,236
stay with you for a lifetime.

642
00:40:11,450 --> 00:40:12,785
How…

643
00:40:13,577 --> 00:40:16,747
can you do something
so cruel to your own child?

644
00:40:19,166 --> 00:40:23,587
Protecting your precious child
is what a father does, isn't it?

645
00:40:30,302 --> 00:40:31,303
I will never…

646
00:40:35,474 --> 00:40:39,770
become a parent like you.

647
00:41:00,749 --> 00:41:03,461
Mr. Kida has apparently
retracted his confession.

648
00:41:05,087 --> 00:41:06,297
Mr. Kamijo.

649
00:41:07,214 --> 00:41:09,300
Could you come talk with us
at the station?

650
00:41:22,229 --> 00:41:23,772
Feels nice outside, right?

651
00:41:23,856 --> 00:41:24,815
Yeah.

652
00:41:32,281 --> 00:41:33,532
Hey!

653
00:41:33,616 --> 00:41:34,575
It's Ryoji!

654
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:37,703
Kanata.

655
00:41:43,459 --> 00:41:45,336
I'm not going anywhere anymore.

656
00:41:47,713 --> 00:41:49,423
From now on, we'll always be together.

657
00:41:55,679 --> 00:41:56,722
I…

658
00:41:58,474 --> 00:42:00,726
will make you and your mom happy.

659
00:42:03,938 --> 00:42:05,147
Got it?

660
00:42:06,232 --> 00:42:07,233
Yeah!

661
00:42:22,331 --> 00:42:23,874
Isn't this great?

662
00:42:27,086 --> 00:42:29,213
The cycle of abuse can be broken.

663
00:42:31,507 --> 00:42:32,758
I will break it.

664
00:42:33,259 --> 00:42:34,510
I will.

665
00:42:46,522 --> 00:42:47,690
Good morning.

666
00:42:58,284 --> 00:43:00,494
Oh, Dr. Masumi.

667
00:43:00,578 --> 00:43:01,912
Good morning.

668
00:43:01,996 --> 00:43:03,372
Sorry for waking you.

669
00:43:03,455 --> 00:43:04,665
It's fine.

670
00:43:04,748 --> 00:43:06,792
It's already this late?

671
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:10,462
Doctor…

672
00:43:13,507 --> 00:43:14,842
Thank you very much.

673
00:43:18,679 --> 00:43:22,099
I am very glad I relied on you,
Dr. Takamori.

674
00:43:25,519 --> 00:43:26,687
Good morning.

675
00:43:26,770 --> 00:43:27,980
Oh! Dr. Masumi!

676
00:43:28,063 --> 00:43:29,273
Good morning.

677
00:43:29,356 --> 00:43:32,443
It was tough without you here.

678
00:43:32,526 --> 00:43:34,320
For Dr. Takamori, it was.

679
00:43:34,403 --> 00:43:35,529
Sure, but…

680
00:43:36,196 --> 00:43:38,282
We should get him
to treat you to something.

681
00:43:38,866 --> 00:43:39,825
No, that's all right.

682
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:50,461
What?

683
00:43:50,544 --> 00:43:52,504
Oh, dear…

684
00:43:52,588 --> 00:43:53,589
Is something wrong?

685
00:43:53,672 --> 00:43:54,840
Well…

686
00:43:54,923 --> 00:43:57,009
- My wife is in labor.
- What?

687
00:43:57,092 --> 00:43:58,886
- She's about to give birth.
- What?

688
00:43:58,969 --> 00:44:00,304
- What should I do?
- Just go!

689
00:44:00,387 --> 00:44:02,097
Don't worry about things here.

690
00:44:02,181 --> 00:44:03,057
I'm going then!

691
00:44:03,140 --> 00:44:04,099
- Take care!
- Sorry.

692
00:44:04,183 --> 00:44:05,934
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Oh, my bag.

693
00:44:07,019 --> 00:44:08,479
- Be careful!
- Thank you.

694
00:44:08,562 --> 00:44:09,938
- See you!
- Bye!

695
00:44:10,022 --> 00:44:11,273
Bye!

696
00:44:23,577 --> 00:44:25,871
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.
